{"lemma":"حارِسٌ","slug":"حارِسٌ","root":"ح.ر.س","root_slug":"ح-ر-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","","n7631"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guard, watchman, guardian, keeper"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"defender"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"governor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"short for حَارِس مَرْمًى (ḥāris marman, “goalkeeper”)","tags":["abbreviation","alt-of"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"guarding, keeping, preserving"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vigilant"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb حَرَسَ (ḥarasa, “to guard”)."},"ipa":["/ħaː.ris/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7631","headword_ar":"حَارِسٌ","root":"Hrs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Guarding, keeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preserving; a guardian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeper:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarasN","text_ar":"حَرَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K) [or this is rather a quasi-pl. n.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~aAsN","text_ar":"حُرَّاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and [pl. of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAsN","text_ar":"اَحْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarasN","text_ar":"حَرَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guards"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a Sultán; (S, * Msb, K TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~aAsN","text_ar":"حُرَّاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) the former is thus used as a gen. n.: (S, Msb:) and the n. un. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarasiY~N","text_ar":"حَرَسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaArisN","text_ar":"حَارِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"unless you mean to denote thereby the signification of guarding, or keeping, without the quality of a gen. n. (S, Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense ironically; (A, Mgh, TA;) because they found guardians to be thieves; (A, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHotarisN","text_ar":"مُحْتَرِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~aAsN","text_ar":"حُرَّاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}